        @Inject
 @Optional
public void setSelection(@Named(value="org.eclipse.ui.selection")
                                              org.eclipse.jface.viewers.ISelection s)
        This method is kept for E3 compatiblity. You can remove it if you do not mix E3 and E4 code.
        With E4 code you will set directly the selection in ESelectionService and you do not receive a ISelection
        Parameters:
        s - the selection received from JFace (E3 mode)

      • setSelection

        @Inject
 @Optional
public void setSelection(@Named(value="org.eclipse.ui.selection")
                                              java.lang.Object o)
        This method manages the selection of your current object. In this example we listen to a single Object (even the ISelection already captured in E3 mode).
        You should change the parameter type of your received Object to manage your specific selection
        Parameters:
        o - : the current object received

      • setSelection

 @Optional
public void setSelection(@Named(value="org.eclipse.ui.selection")
                                              java.lang.Object[] selectedObjects)
        This method manages the multiple selection of your current objects.
        You should change the parameter type of your array of Objects to manage your specific selection
        Parameters:
        selectedObjects - : the current array of objects received in case of multiple selection
